#1 ESP8266 (Transmitter): Used to collect water level data and transmit via LoRa.
#2 ESP32 (Receiver): Receives water level data and displays it on the TFT display.
#3 LoRa SX1278 Module: Long-range communication module for transmitting data.
#4 Water Level Sensors Stainless steel probes: connected to the ESP8266 GPIO pins for detecting various water levels.
#5 1.8" TFT Display: Used with the receiver to display the current water level and signal strength.
#6 Other Components: Resistors, pull-down circuitry, power supply, wiring, and PCB for connections.
